summary: An email from a paralegal specialist at the U.S. Attorney's Office for the SDNY, summarizing an analysis of phone records. The analysis found that two victim phone numbers had no direct contact with numbers attributed to Ghislaine Maxwell, but did have contact with a third party. The timing of calls between Maxwell and this third party was noted in relation to calls between the third party and the victims.

persons.name: Ghislaine Maxwell
persons.context: Her attributed phone numbers are analyzed for contact with victim numbers. The email notes calls between her and an unnamed third party around the time that third party contacted victims.

persons.name: Paralegal Specialist

persons.context: Author of the email, summarizing the phone record analysis and attaching relevant documents.

connections.description: Phone records show calls between a number attributed to Maxwell and a number attributed to an unnamed third party.
Phone records show the unnamed third party's number was in contact with victim phone numbers.

events.title: Phone Record Analysis Summary
events.description: A paralegal specialist emails colleagues with an analysis of phone records, finding a temporal link between calls involving Ghislaine Maxwell, an unnamed third party, and victim contacts.

keyFacts: Phone records analysis found two victim phone numbers had no direct contact with numbers attributed to Ghislaine Maxwell.
Both victim numbers were found in the phone records of an unnamed third party.
In three instances, calls between Maxwell and the third party occurred around the same time (within the same hour or directly before) as calls between the third party and a victim.
The document is an internal email from the U.S. Attorney's Office for the SDNY, indicating ongoing investigative work in late 2021.
